{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὕμνος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>hymn, ode, in praise</b> of gods or heroes (καί τι ἦν εἶδος ῳδῆς εὐχαὶ πρὸς θεούς, ὄνομα δὲ ὕμνοι ἐπεκαλοῦντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 700b; ὕμνους θεοῖς καὶ ἐγκώμια τοῖς ἀγαθοῖς [prev. author] “R.” 607a, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1448b27), once in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, ἀοιδῆς ὕμνος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.429 (followed by Demodocus' song of the Wooden Horse, 499ff)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὕμνῳ νικήσαντα φέρειν τρίποδ᾽ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 657; ἀνδρῶν τε παλαιῶν ἠδὲ γυναικῶν ὕμνον ἀείδουσιν “hymnus ad Apollinem” 161; frequently in 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus, ὕμνος πολύφατος, ἐπικώμιος, etc., “O.” 1.8, “N.” 8.50, +others; Θήρωνος Ὀλυμπιονίκαν ὕμνον “O.” 3.3; and in 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus, ὑφάνας ὕμνον 5.10, compare 6.11, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὕμνοι θεῶν <b>to</b> or <b>in honour of</b> the gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 801d; τιμῶν θεὰν ὕμνοισιν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 56; τοὺς χοροὺς.. καὶ τοὺς ὕ. τῷ θεῷ ποιεῖτε 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.51, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 177a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὕμνοι Δαυείδ <b>psalms</b> of [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: David Philosophus, LXX.2Ch.7.6; ψαλμοὶ καὶ ὕ. καὶ ᾠδαί NT.Eph.5.19 \">NT+6th c.AD+</a>]: in Trag. also of <b>mournful songs,</b> addressed to gods or heroes, τὸν δυσκέλαδον ὕ. Ἐρινύος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 868 (Lyric poetry), compare “Pers.” 620, 625 (_anapaest meter_), “Ch.” 475 (Lyric poetry); ὕ. ἐξ Ἐρινύων, δέσμιος φρενῶν, ἀφόρμικτος [prev. author] “Eu.” 331 (Lyric poetry), compare 306; ἐν ἀλύροις κλέοντες ὕμνοις 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 447 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὕ. Ἅιδου, of one whose songs are death, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista Comedy texts 69 (Lyric poetry).\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —On ὕμνοι of various kinds see Men.Rh.p.333 [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus; ὁ κυρίως ὕ. πρὸς κιθάραν ᾔδετο ἑστώτων 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “Chr.” cited in 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc. “Bibliotheca - Patrologia Graeca” p.320 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus, compare 1st c.BC: Didymus Grammaticus cited in “Etymologicum Magnum” 777.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. [Most commonly ῡ, but only by position; ῠ proved by εὔῠμνος (which see), ῠμνῳδεῖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 990 (Lyric poetry), ῠμνήσω 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 72 (Lyric poetry).] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5215","accentedUnicode":"ὕμνος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5214","matchingForm":"ὑμνέω","stepTransliteration":"humneō","gloss":"to praise","_zh_tw_Gloss":"唱了詩, 要頌揚","_es_Gloss":"alabar","_zh_Gloss":"唱了诗, 要颂扬"}],"shortDef":"hymn, song of praise","mediumDef":"<b>a song; a hymn, song of praise</b>, to God, <ref='Eph.5.19'>Eph. 5:19;</ref> <ref='Col.3.16'>Col. 3:16</ref>*","stepGloss":"hymn","stepTransliteration":"humnos","count":2,"_es_Definition":"himno","_zh_tw_Definition":"讚美詩歌","_zh_Definition":"赞美诗歌","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"thánh ca; thánh nhạc","_zh_tw_Gloss":"頌詞","_es_Gloss":"himno","_zh_Gloss":"颂词"}]}